What this battery tests

The suite systematically tests:

1. Random-seed stability.
2. Learning rates.
3. Hard-negative versus random-negative ratios.
4. Semantic, hierarchy-only, and hybrid negative selection.
5. Full-context versus title-only and other field-ablation variants.
6. Binary cross-entropy, RankNet, ListNet, and LambdaLoss.
7. Small, medium, large, and extra-large training budgets.
8. Input sequence lengths of 256, 384, and 512 tokens.
9. One, three, five, and eight historical prototype examples per code.
10. Candidate retrieval pools of 20, 30, 50, and 80 codes.
11. Balanced class sampling versus production-frequency sampling.
12. Weak-SOC-group oversampling.
13. Separate target models versus shared SOC and shared NAICS/SOC models.
14. Optional MiniLM-L12 and BGE reranker base models.
15. Five-seed, larger-budget confirmation of the best screening recipes.

Sentence Transformers officially supports the BCE and listwise/pairwise ranking losses used here, including RankNet, ListNet, and LambdaLoss. Its listwise losses use query, candidate-list, and relevance-list training records, which the enhanced trainer now creates.  

The negative-mining tests are also deliberate. Sentence Transformers notes that strong hard negatives are important for Cross-Encoder training, but training exclusively on difficult negatives can reduce easy-case performance, so the battery separately tests semantic negatives, hierarchy negatives, and mixtures containing random negatives.  

Two different evaluations are calculated

Every experiment reports both:

Oracle reranking: the true code is guaranteed to be in the candidate list. This isolates how well the Cross-Encoder ranks candidates.

Retrieval-pipeline evaluation: the true code is not artificially inserted. This measures candidate generation plus reranking together.

It also calculates candidate recall at:

Top 1
Top 4
Top 10
Top 20
Top 40

This distinction is crucial:

High oracle performance + low candidate recall
= improve retrieval/candidate generation.
High candidate recall + low oracle improvement
= improve reranker training.
Both high
= recipe is a serious promotion candidate.

